We have recommended the following:

1. Justify why these various disbursements were granted;

2. Stop the practice of granting cash advances to elected official unless for their official traveling expenses only; 

3. Faithful adherence to the above-cited provision is hereby enjoined, otherwise, disallowed in audit.

We have recommended to management the following:

Plan all procurement meticulously and judiciously;

Justify why Management sorted to granting of cash advances for such payments without going through the process of public bidding; 

3. Faithful adherence to the above-cited provision is hereby enjoined, otherwise, disallowed in audit

We have recommended to management the following:
1. Justify the delayed completion of various projects and furnish the approved time extensions to our office (if there’s any);

2. Direct the Municipal Engineer to prioritize and to fast tract the implementation of the LGU’s P/P/As;

3. Send a written demand to the contractors for the full and satisfactory performance of their obligations under their respective contract with the municipal government;

4. Enforce the provisions in the contract particularly the aspect on liquidated damages in congruence with the provisions on liquidated damages under RA 9184; and

5. Carefully and judiciously review and re-evaluate the necessary qualifications of the contractor as to its manpower compliment, financial capacity to undertake the contract, availability of the require heavy equipment for the contract and status of prior contract entered into by the supplier/contractor as to how satisfactory they were in their execution or performance of their obligation.

Recommendation:
We have recommended that management consider the following:
Justify the delayed completion of various projects and furnish the approved time extensions to our office (if there’s any);
Direct the Municipal Engineer to prioritize and to fast tract the implementation of the LGU’s P/P/As;
Send a written demand to the contractors for the full and satisfactory performance of their obligations under their respective contract with the municipal government;
Enforce the provisions in the contract particularly the aspect on liquidated damages in congruence with the provisions on liquidated damages under RA 9184; and
Carefully and judiciously review and re-evaluate the necessary qualifications of the contractor as to its manpower compliment, financial capacity to undertake the contract, availability of the require heavy equipment for the contract and status of prior contract entered into by the supplier/contractor as to how satisfactory they were in their execution or performance of their obligation.

