We have recommended the Municipal Treasurer to:

Justify why collections are not deposited intact daily or the next banking day;

Require the Municipal Treasurer to timely deposit her collections;

Allow Accountable Officers to request accountable forms only after previous accountable forms were remitted;

Require to strictly follow the provisions of COA Memorandum No. 2013-004 dated July 9, 2013.

Recommendation:
We have recommended the Municipal Treasurer to:
Justify why collections are not deposited intact daily or the next banking day;
Require the Municipal Treasurer to timely deposit her collections;
Allow Accountable Officers to request accountable forms only after previous accountable forms were remitted;
Require to strictly follow the provisions of COA Memorandum No. 2013-004 dated July 9, 2013

a.Actual physical inventory-taking of the properties should be undertaken and Report on the Physical Count of Property Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) be prepared and submitted;
b. Require the Municipal Treasurer and Municipal Accountant to maintain Property Cards, Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards for each category of assets, and Real Property Ledger Cards for land;
